  "description": "The main thing about this stub-tailed wren, was the orange overall color, including the throat. See photos.Behaviors: Staying low, other birds present were: Ruby-crowned Kinglets, Hermit Thrushes, Dark-eyed Juncos, Orange-crowned and Wilson's Warblers, also a Hammond's Flycatcher.Call: I heard a bird chipping softly, that sounded similar to a Wilson's Warbler chip. Giving two noted calls. I saw the bird, and it was a very orangy stub tail wren.Plumage: fall",
